# Backlog Management Rules

**`docs/BACKLOG.md` is exclusively owned by the backlog-manager agent.**
No other agent, orchestrator, or Cursor session may edit this file directly.
If you need to update the backlog, invoke the backlog-manager agent.

Read `.claude/agents/backlog-manager/AGENT.md` for the full agent spec.

## File ownership

All work items live in `docs/BACKLOG.md`. Humans own structure and priorities.
Only the backlog-manager agent may write to this file. All other agents MUST
delegate backlog edits to the backlog-manager.

## Rules for the backlog-manager

### After completing a task

1. Read `docs/BACKLOG.md`
2. Mark completed items: change `- [ ]` to `- [x]` with today's date
3. Update "Recently Completed" as appropriate
4. Prune "Recently Completed" — keep only the last 5–10 items

### When adding items

Every item must have enough detail for an AI engineer to implement without
asking questions: what, where (file paths), how (when non-obvious), why
(rationale/constraints), and a `#backend`/`#frontend`/`#fullstack` tag.

### When near-term work is thin

1. Point to the next unchecked items in phase order within `docs/BACKLOG.md`
2. Wait for human approval before adding new checklist lines

### What NOT to do

- Do NOT edit `docs/BACKLOG.md` if you are not the backlog-manager agent
- Do NOT rewrite phases or narrative without explicit human instruction
- Do NOT add speculative items without approval
- Do NOT remove items unless completed or explicitly cancelled
- Do NOT reorder items — the human decides priority
- Do NOT add items that lack sufficient implementation detail
